25/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Nearly 70 per cent of the public say they would support the county's NATO entry in a possible referendum, according to a poll by the Institute for Democracy, Solidarity and Civic Society.
The results, released Friday (25 June), found that 14 per cent would vote against Alliance membership, while 13.5 per cent described themselves as undecided.
Overall, the poll suggested that most have a positive view about the benefits of NATO membership.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 25/06/04)
